{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Extreme gradient boosting (XGBoost)XGBoost is one of the most representative ensemble ML algorithms under the gradient boosting framework [43].It has been shown to achieve state-of-the-art (SOTA) performance on many standard classification benchmark datasets [37,68,69].",
    "Seven hyperparameters were optimized: learning_rate (0.01-0.1), n_estimators (50-100), max_depth (3)(4)(5), min_child_weight (1-3), gamma (0-0.1), subsample (0.8-1.0), and colsample bytree (0.8-1.0).",
    "Deep neural networks (DNN)DNN is essentially an artificial neural network with an input layer, an output layer, and multiple hidden layers, which mimics the behavior of biological neural networks [44].",
    "DNN consists of a large number of individual neurons [70,71], and each neuron in the DNN architecture collects information from its associated neurons and a non-linear activation function was then used to activate the aggregated information.",
    "Three hyperparameters were optimized: dropouts (0.1, 0.2, 0.5), layer_sizes (64,128,256,512) and weight_decay_penalty (0.01, 0.001, 0.0001)."
  ],
